data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_Created
data.value: The request succeeded, and a new resource was created as a result

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_Accepted
data.value: The request has been received but not yet acted upon

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_NoContent
data.value: There is no content to send for this request, but the headers may be useful

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_BadRequest
data.value: The server cannot or will not process the request due to something that is perceived to be a client error

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_Unauthorized
data.value: The client must authenticate itself to get the requested response

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_PaymentRequired
data.value: The client must have payment information to get the requested response

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_Forbidden
data.value: The client does not have access rights to the content; that is, it is unauthorized, so the server is refusing to give the requested resource

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_NotFound
data.value: The server cannot find the requested resource

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_MethodNotAllowed
data.value: The request is not allowed by the current state of the resource

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_Conflict
data.value: The request conflicts with the current state of the resource

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_Locked
data.value: The current resource is locked and cannot be accessed

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_UnsupportedMediaType
data.value: The client has made a request to Accept a media type that is not supported by the server

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_TooManyRequests
data.value: The client has made too many requests in a specific timeframe

data.name: HttpConstants_StatusCodes_Reason_InternalServerError
data.value: An unexpected error occured on the server, which should not have happened in normal operation
